<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 22 at 1:35PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT...
WEATHER...
* Temperatures will continue to hover around the freezing mark
through the afternoon hours as pockets of freezing rain
continue to occur over the Tri-Cities region, and especially
interior portions of Midland and Bay counties.
* Freezing rain rates up to 0.02 inch per hour will continue to be
possible, leading to light icing accumulating on area roadways
and surfaces especially those that remain untreated.
IMPACTS...
* Light icing will lead to hazardous conditions on untreated
roads and walking surfaces.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for hazardous
driving conditions by slowing down and allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
